141 victims of the terrorist attack at Domodedovo received payments from the airport.
141 people received charitable payments from the Aviation Fund, which was created by the management of Domodedovo airport to help the victims of the terrorist attack in 2011, Interfax reports.
According to airport spokesman Alexander Vlasov, two more applications are currently under consideration.
"The Foundation continues to make charitable payments to the victims of the terrorist attack in 2011 and provides comprehensive assistance in resolving existing issues," added Vlasov, recalling that the Foundation's website, which contains full information on the procedure for rendering charitable assistance, was created specifically to facilitate interaction with the victims.
