PokÃ©mon Go, a decent hunt for health and happiness
It is fascinating to see how the world is changing.
That teenagers and children no longer go out to play, preferring to spend their free time staring at screens, has been a complaint of many over the past decade.
Pokemon Go takes people off the couch and into some physical activity.
Screen time was initially limited to TV, then video games and, more recently, smartphones.
