According to the regulator, JSC JSCB GAZSTROIBANK pursued a high-risk lending policy related to the placement of funds in low-quality assets.
Adequate risk assessment at the request of the supervisory authority and a reliable reflection of the value of the bank's assets led to the emergence of grounds for the credit institution to implement bankruptcy prevention measures.
In addition, the credit institution was involved in dubious transit operations.
A temporary administration has been appointed at the bank for the period of validity until the appointment of a bankruptcy administrator or liquidator.
The powers of the executive bodies of a credit institution are suspended in accordance with federal laws.
JSC JSCB GAZSTROIBANK is a member of the deposit insurance system.
It should be recalled that, in accordance with Federal Law No. 177-FZ "On insurance of deposits of individuals in banks of the Russian Federation," the payment of insurance indemnity to bank depositors, including individual entrepreneurs, is envisaged in the amount of 100% of the balance, but not more than 1.4 million roubles in total per depositor.
Payments, according to the Deposit Insurance Agency, will begin no later than 26 August 2016.
