Kommersant-News - The new general contractor promises to deliver Zenit Arena by 26 December.
Metrostroy, the new general contractor of the stadium under construction in St. Petersburg, which is to host matches for the 2017 Confederations Cup and the 2018 FIFA World Cup, promises to deliver the arena by 26 December, reports RIA Novosti, with reference to Vadim Tyulpanov, head of the temporary commission of the Federation Council on preparations for the 2018 FIFA World Cup.
"Today, we visited the construction site together with the Minister of Sport of Russia, Vitaly Mutko, and the General Director of Metrostroy, Vadim Aleksandrov, was with us.
He said he would hand over the stadium by December 26.
It is a serious St. Petersburg company, it never breaks the deadlines.
Vitaly Mutko and I were happy with what we saw and heard, "the agency quotes an interlocutor as saying.
Earlier, Vitaly Mutko arrived in St. Petersburg to inspect the venue for the upcoming large-scale competitions.
Mr. Tyulpanov also noted that the Commission of the Council of the Federal Federation headed by him will continue to monitor the progress of construction of the stadium and will regularly visit the construction site.
To recall, yesterday it became known that Metrostroy will complete the construction of Zenit Arena, the value of the contract will be about 5.4 billion roubles. The same company won a tender for the improvement of the area around the stadium, the value of the contract will be 2.4 billion roubles. Contracts with JSC Transstroy Corporation, LLC Engineering Corporation Transstroy-SPb and JSC Engineering Corporation Transstroy have been terminated.
Two other companies were not allowed to compete for the construction of the stadium.
For more information about the choice of a new general contractor, read Kommersant's material: "Metrostroy was let into the field."
